    <title>You Know Where to Find Me</title>
    <link href="http://blog.zealoft.com/2016/10/13/You-Know-Where-to-Find-Me/"/>
    <id>http://blog.zealoft.com/2016/10/13/You-Know-Where-to-Find-Me/</id>
    <published>2016-10-14T00:23:54.000Z</published>
    <updated>2016-10-15T04:58:31.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>I now proudly live an open-sourced life.</p>
<a id="more"></a>
<iframe frameborder="no" border="0" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" width="330" height="86" src="http://music.163.com/outchain/player?type=2&id=28930654&auto=1&height=66"></iframe>

<p>I’ve been thinking for a while about writing a page to sharing my life.</p>
<p>I share my schedule so that people know where I am, what I am doing and what I am going to do. Therefore, whenever you want to join my life, you always know when and where to. Want to watch a movie with me? Sure, check my schedule: If I’m free, I’m free. See I’m running and want to join? Great, I would love to have someone run with me. You can add new events into my life. Isn’t it fun? My life is now open-sourced. It’s like a git repository: you can fork it or submit a pull request, and I can merge your “code” into my master branch.</p>
<p>It also helps me to keep up with my schedule. Many planned events are not accomplished just because I feel lazy. However, I need to keep my words to make this page credible. I promise that you will find me as this page indicates.</p>
<p>I wish to receive your pull requests soon.</p>
<p>Sincerely,</p>
<p>Jim</p>
]]></content>
    
